    "id": "ddx-b5816493",
    "title": "bead-lifecycle: add stable rule_fingerprint to intake.blocked entries with dedup",
    "description": "PROBLEM\nintake.blocked entries appended by readiness lack a stable identifier, so identical rerun conditions stack duplicate warnings on every pass.\n\nROOT CAUSE\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:2784-2815 constructs the intake.blocked entry without a rule_fingerprint and performs no dedup against existing entries before appending.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\nExtend the intake.blocked entry schema with a rule_fingerprint field computed as a stable hash over (rule_id, bead_id, sorted evidence keys that drove the rule). Before appending a new entry, scan existing intake.blocked entries on the bead and skip the append when a matching rule_fingerprint already exists. Keep hash inputs deterministic (sorted keys, canonical encoding) so reruns with identical inputs produce identical fingerprints.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- operator_override field (sibling child bead).\n- `ddx bead show` rendering (sibling child bead).\n- Adding new readiness rules or changing rule evaluation logic.\n- Changing the readiness terminal flow itself.\n- Updating FEAT-010/ADR-023 policy text.\n- Fizeau concrete route selection, model ranking, provider fallback, or profile catalog behavior.\n- Rewriting execute-bead branch merge policy.\n- Changing post-attempt review terminal outcomes that already carry concrete evidence for operator action.\n\nPARENT/DEPS\nParent: ddx-cc0641a7.",
    "acceptance": "1. TestIntakeBlockedCarriesRuleFingerprint asserts every intake.blocked entry emitted by readiness has a non-empty rule_fingerprint that is stable across reruns with identical inputs.\n2. TestIntakeBlockedFingerprintDedupes asserts running readiness twice with identical inputs appends the entry only once (second pass is a no-op for an existing fingerprint).\n3. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... ./internal/bead/... ./cmd/...` green.\n4. `lefthook run pre-commit` passing.",
